<h3>Which manual to read first?</h3>

<ul>
	<li>(#1) Since you are in CAP, CAP&rsquo;s Drill and Ceremonies manual (CAPP60-33) takes priority.</li>
	<li>(#1) The CAP uniform manual (CAPR 39-1) is the only uniform manual CAP members should follow when wearing CAP uniforms.</li>
	<li>(#1) For customs, courtesies, Respect on Display</li>
	<li>(#1) Flag etiquette resources</li>
	<li>(#2) If something is not covered in any of these manuals, the AFMAN Drill and Ceremonies 36-2203 is the next place to look since CAP is an auxiliary of the Air Force.</li>
	<li>(#3) The Drill Master is an informative site and may help expand your planning and reasoning skills with color guard. However, everything stated here should be checked by the manuals listed above. It covers all military branches and JROTC, so you want to make sure you follow CAP-specific protocol correctly.</li>
	<li><a href="https://thedrillmaster.org/">The Drillmaster Home</a></li>
</ul>

<h3>How to Join</h3>

<p data-end="140" data-start="96">The Scottsdale Color Guard is a prestigious unit that represents our squadron, precision, and pride. Joining the Color Guard is more than just a position it&rsquo;s an opportunity to develop leadership, teamwork, and personal discipline while being part of a tradition that inspires school and community spirit.</p>

<p data-end="491" data-start="460"><strong data-end="489" data-start="460">Eligibility Requirements:</strong></p>

<ul data-end="726" data-start="492">
	<li data-end="520" data-start="492">
	<p data-end="520" data-start="494">Must be a current cadet.&nbsp;</p>
	</li>
	<li data-end="520" data-start="492">
	<p data-end="520" data-start="494">Must have a set of&nbsp;class B blues.</p>
	</li>
	<li data-end="576" data-start="521">
	<p data-end="576" data-start="523">Must be proficient in drill movements and commands.</p>
	</li>
	<li data-end="726" data-start="651">
	<p data-end="726" data-start="653">Must be willing to participate in events, ceremonies, and competitions.&nbsp;</p>
	</li>
	<li data-end="726" data-start="651">
	<p data-end="726" data-start="653">Must be willing to do extra drill training before squadron meetings.</p>
	</li>
</ul>

<p data-end="751" data-start="728"><strong data-end="749" data-start="728">What You&rsquo;ll Gain:</strong></p>

<ul data-end="1063" data-start="752">
	<li data-end="811" data-start="752">
	<p data-end="811" data-start="754">Advanced training in drill, flag, and rifle techniques.</p>
	</li>
	<li data-end="892" data-start="812">
	<p data-end="892" data-start="814">Leadership and teamwork skills that will serve you in cadet life and beyond.</p>
	</li>
	<li data-end="991" data-start="893">
	<p data-end="991" data-start="895">The honor of representing Scottsdale at school events, community ceremonies, and competitions.</p>
	</li>
	<li data-end="1063" data-start="992">
	<p data-end="1063" data-start="994">A supportive, motivated team that encourages growth and excellence.</p>
	</li>
</ul>

<p data-end="1273" data-start="1065"><strong data-end="1082" data-start="1065">How to Apply:</strong><br data-end="1085" data-start="1082" />
If you meet the eligibility requirements and are ready to dedicate yourself to excellence, speak with your flight cadre&nbsp;or the Color Guard commander to begin the application process.</p>

<p><strong>Important:</strong> The manuals can be confusing, especially when updated sections are published. Before correcting a traditional practice of your team, make sure you understand the manual accurately and are referencing a relevant section by checking that others come to the same conclusion you have.</p>
